728012f-b.title: Queens: Springfield Boulevard - 47th Avenue
728012f-b.text:
Springfield Boulevard, east side, at 47th Avenue, showing
the Platt Carll House, a yellow shingled home. Carll was the
owner in 1860 and J. O'Donnell in 1873-1909. Platt Carll was
sheriff of Flushing and dealt in cattle. The entrance to the
O'Donnell property was on Rocky Hill Road, which at this point
is now (1941) 216th Street, the house having been situated at
the southwestern tip of Douglas Pond, the present Oakland Lake.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  1923
MAY BE REPRODUCED  Views 1,2,3
